le col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr class=\"header\">\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Who we’ve asked for a response</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"30%\"><strong>Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Maria Loucas</td>\r\n<td>How soon can residents return to St Basil’s once they are confirmed COVID-19 negative?</td>\r\n<td>DHHS -PHU</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td width=\"20%\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>John Bahtsevanoglou</td>\r\n<td>What are the options when discharged from hospital? What is the timeline?</td>\r\n<td>VACRC</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>What are our respite options whilst long term options are considered?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Charlie Lawrence</td>\r\n<td>What special dispensations are available to St Basil’s families for option other than St Basil’s repatriation?\r\n\r\nCan the 30-day notification period be waived?</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>What other RACFs can St Basil’s families consider and what financial incentives will be given?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>If families take the 8 weeks home support option, will St Basil’s provide the equipment required?</td>\r\n<td>ACP/DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>St Basil’s provide the equipment required?</td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">Repatriation Protocol</h2>\r\n	\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vicky</td>\r\n<td>Families no longer have faith in residential aged care facilities:\r\n\r\na.     What alternative residential aged care facilities are available to St Basil’s residents?\r\n\r\nb.     Can they receive reassurance that these facilities are safe?\r\n\r\nc.      Families need a checklist of decision-making criteria that will ensure them that the facility is safe.\r\n\r\nd.     How will the families gather the answers to the checklist?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Doh (a)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nACQSC (b – d)</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>What are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC/ ACP</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vaia Toussas</td>\r\n<td>What are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Peter</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Infection control – ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Will the department ensure the families that residents will not return until permission has been given by family?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC/ DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Nikki Kontos</td>\r\n<td>How often will COVID-19 testing be conducted when residents return?</td>\r\n<td>DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Document the role of the Commission in making sure no one is sent back to St Basil’s unless it’s safe?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n	\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">Bereavement</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Spiros Dimitriou</td>\r\n<td>What support is available to families that have lost loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat support is available to families that have lost loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Mia</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nWhat support is available to families that have lost loved ones?</td>\r\n<td>DoH</td>\r\n<td>Wed 18th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">ACQSC Audit &amp; VIC Coronial Inquiry</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Christine Golding</td>\r\n<td>How is the ACQSC going to conduct an audit when St Basil’s is not open and during lockdown? What is the step-by-step process of the audit?</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>John Bahtsevanoglou</td>\r\n<td>During the audit and inquiry:\r\n\r\nWhat are the standards and process to ensure St Basil’s is safe to return?\r\n\r\nThe families would like to know the detail regarding the process, the specific steps, timeframe for each step and the metrics (that can be used on an ongoing basis) that will used to determine if St Basil’s is safe.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>ACQSC/ ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Who will make a representation to the Victorian Coronial inquiry?</td>\r\n<td>DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Does the Victorian Coronial inquiry cover both COVID-19 positive and negative cases?</td>\r\n<td>DHHS</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #7030A0\">Protocol</h2>\r\n<table class=\"core-table col-rules\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Family </strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Question to government</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Owner</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Due Date</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Response/Answer</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Spiros Dimitriou</td>\r\n<td>Did St Basils management report the first COVID case within the required period of time as per \"first 24hr report\" and then follow process as stated in that report.</td>\r\n<td>ACP - DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Ralph</td>\r\n<td>How were residents kept isolated in their rooms once the first case of COVID was reported? Please explain the process that was undertaken</td>\r\n<td>ACP - DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Duplicate Question:\r\n\r\nHow were residents kept isolated in their rooms once the first case of COVID was reported? Please explain the process that was undertaken</td>\r\n<td>ACP DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Did St Basil’s deploy an infection control plan after the first case was known, and what was it?</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ DoH/ACQSC – Independent reviewer</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>Why were St Basil’s Management unable to contain the virus from spreading throughout the nursing home?</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>?</td>\r\n<td>What training was provided to staff on infection control and correct use of PPE? Please specify dates and type of training conducted</td>\r\n<td>ACP</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>DUPLICATE QUESTION:\r\n\r\nWhat training was provided to staff on infection control and correct use of PPE? Please specify dates and type of training conducted</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ ACQSC</td>\r\n<td>Mon 24th</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Tony Papantoniou</td>\r\n<td>What infection control plan was executed at St Basil’s once the first COVID positive case was found?</td>\r\n<td>ACP/ACQSC</